<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Egypt-Crash     09-30 0091</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Egypt-Crash,0092</SECOND>
<HEAD>Trains Crash in Egypt, Four Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAIRO, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two passenger trains crashed on the
outskirts of Cairo after one ignored signal lights, killing four
people and injuring 46, a news report said.
   The accident occurred Friday when one of the trains smashed into
the other as it made a stop in the Nile Delta town of Qalyub, the
Middle East News Agency said. It quoted a statement by the Egyptian
Railway Authority.
   The agency gave no further details. It said only that
investigations were under way.
</TEXT>
