<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--India-Protests     09-30 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--India-Protests,0197</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Fire On Protesters, Kill Five</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SRINAGAR, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police fired on crowds protesting the
arrest of a separatist leader in northern Jammu-Kashmir state,
killing at least five people and wounding 75, officials said.
   Authorities imposed a curfew and deployed soldiers in Anantnag,
where three people were killed by police gunfire Friday, a
government spokesman said. Protesters set fire to official jeeps
and threw homemade bombs at government buildings, he said.
   A fourth person was shot dead by police gunfire during protests
in Sopore town, and a fifth died and 15 were wounded when police
fired on crowds in Srinagar, the spokesman said.
   Demonstrators were protesting the arrest of Shabir Ahmed Shah,
leader of the People's League, the spokesman said on condition of
anonymity.
   The People's League is an underground group calling for the
state to secede from India and join Pakistan. Shah, who calls for
armed struggle to achieve the group's aims, was arrested Thursday,
the spokesman said.
   India and Pakistan both claim Jammu-Kashmir and have fought
three wars over the state since both countries gained independence
from Britain in 1947. Jammu-Kashmir is India's only mainly Moslem
state.
</TEXT>
