   A teacher is hoping for a
brief reunion with Mick Jagger after living with him in London 30
years ago.
   ``Well, I didn't actually live with him,'' Gillian Bloom said,
laughing. ``I lived as a boarder in his parents' house for about a
year.''
   Bloom remembers the then-16-year-old Jagger well. He played his
guitar in the garage at all hours, she said.
   ``I was 20 at the time and studying at Dartford College to be a
physical education teacher. Mick's parents were always telling him
to turn down the volume so I could study.
   ``Isn't that laughable? To think I might have killed Mick
Jagger's career by studying too much!''
   Bloom hopes to meet Jagger when the band performs at B.C. Place
Stadium in Vancouver Nov. 1 and 2.
