<HEAD>HUD Says No To Cleveland Grant For Rock 'N' Roll Hall Of Fame</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The federal government has rejected
Cleveland's request for $6.9 million to help build a Rock 'N' Roll
Hall of Fame, but city officials say it's too soon to declare an
end to its music fantasy.
   Development officials Greg Shumate and Chris Johnson say they'll
quickly review funding commitments _ including those dependent on
