<FIRST>r a PM-ZsaZsaNotebook 1stLd-Writethru a0457 09-30 0668</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Zsa Zsa Notebook, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0457,0684</SECOND>
<HEAD>From the Start, Zsa Zsa Trial Highlighted by Theatrics</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Zsa Zsa Trial, Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 8th graf, `Every Girl ...' with 1 graf to fix spelling
of `Moulin Rouge.' Picks up 9th graf, `Television viewers ...'.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JEFF WILSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In all of Zsa Zsa Gabor's roles,
from the movie ``Queen of Outer Space'' to TV's ``Merv Griffin
Show,'' nothing quite compared to the performance she delivered in
her cop-slapping trial.
   At times indignant, other times irrational, the temperamental
Hungarian actress' theatrics riveted crowds of reporters for 15
days.
   In the end, though, her courtroom dramatics didn't convince the
jury of her innocence. Miss Gabor was convicted of three of four
misdemeanor counts on Friday.
   From the start _ her curbside arrest and handcuffing on June 14
for slapping motorcycle policeman Paul Kramer _ Miss Gabor couldn't
believe she would be treated like common folk instead of the
``princess'' she insisted she was.
   After all, she said, she's a Hollywood glamor queen, actress and
housewife.
   When she struck Kramer in the slap heard round the world, she
asked, ``Who do you think you are?'' Kramer responded, ``Who do you
think YOU are?''
   ``I am the daughter of a freedom fighter,'' the flamboyant
actress told reporters during her trial. ``I am a horsewoman,'' she
frequently intoned. ``I am a princess. I am Zsa Zsa.''
   ``Every Girl Should Have One'' in 1978 was Zsa Zsa's last film
role. Other movie credits include ``Moulin Rouge,'' ``Boys Night
Out'' and ``Picture Mommy Dead.''
   Television viewers are familiar with Miss Gabor's frequent talk
show appearances, as one of the celebrity squares on ``Hollywood
Squares'' and on ``The Munsters'' reruns. She'll be on this
season's first episode of ``The Munsters Today.''
   Miss Gabor, believed older than the 66 she claims, has a
cosmetics and jewelry business, commands about $5,000 for her TV
appearances and has extensive real estate holdings.
   She pulled out all the stops throughout her trial, drawn to
microphones as if they were diamonds.
   She blasted the prosecutor's ``Napoleon complex,'' insulted gays
and lesbians, dismissed witnesses as punks or drug users, and
pulled courtroom antics that ranged from sobs and laughter to
stomping out of court in a huff.
   Among the highlights:
   _After Deputy District Attorney Elden Fox characterized Miss
Gabor as a spoiled aristocrat who didn't know the meaning of truth,
Miss Gabor burst into tears and left the courtroom. The actress
said she was going to Europe.
   _When the jury began deliberations, the prosecutor said he was
offended by the behavior of the media. Reporters converged daily on
the unpredictable Miss Gabor for her latest observation.
   ``It did bother me,'' Fox said. ``It's sort of like an unsavory
symbiotic relationship between the media and the defendant in this
case. It's sort of like they feed on each other.''
   _Miss Gabor said in the first week of her trial that she was
afraid to go to jail because jails are filled with lesbians. The
controversy lingered throughout the trial, with Miss Gabor
attempting to clarify the remark and insisting she didn't mean to
offend gays.
   _She also talked often about ``that gorgeous'' officer, Kramer,
but didn't conceal her dislike for him.
   ``He's a vulgar policeman and he's a liar,'' she said. ``I
should have scratched his eyes out. I think that cop is not too
bright. I think he must be very spoiled because he's very sexy.
He's gorgeous. He's sexy, but I don't like that man.''
   _Kramer was hospitalized during the trial after crashing his
motorcycle into a police car while chasing suspects through Beverly
Hills. Miss Gabor suggested the crash was a staged sympathy ploy.
   _Miss Gabor's husband, who told a reporter it would be OK to
call him prince or Freddy, got into a spat with the actress over
her constant reference to Kramer as gorgeous. Miss Gabor slapped
her husband-prince and broke his glasses.
   ``German men love to suffer,'' she said.
</TEXT>
