<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``The old line that one man's terrorist is another man's freedom
fighter is absolutely wrong. One man's terrorist is another man's
terrorist.'' _ Augustus Richard Norton, a professor at the U.S.
Military Academy at West Point, N.Y., at a meeting in Santa Monica,
Calif., of the U.S.-Soviet Task Force to Prevent Terrorism.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``A new world war is being waged by an aggressor unrestrained by
the traditional rules of engagement or by the responsibilities of
national sovereignty.'' _ President Virgilio Barco of Colombia,
declaring drug barons are at war with the world in a speech to the
U.N. General Assembly calling upon all nations to sign the Vienna
Convention on narcotics trafficking.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``I've been on this job for 25 years, and I've never seen so
much dope in one place. I couldn't believe it,'' _ John M. Zienter,
a Drug Enforcement Administration special agent in Los Angeles,
after 20 tons of cocaine worth $2 billion wholesale was seized in
the world's biggest cocaine bust.
