<FIRST>r a PM-JammedUzi     09-30 0239</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Jammed Uzi,0247</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Say Two Gunmen Arrested After Their Guns Jam</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WATERBURY, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men attempted to fire into a crowd
with an Uzi submachine gun and a semiautomatic pistol but their
guns jammed, police said.
   ``If their guns hadn't jammed, we'd of had a bloodbath, a real
massacre,'' Chief Inspector John Griffin said Friday.
   Arthur Little, 19, and Daniel Hampton, 21, both of New York
City, were arrested and charged with criminal attempt at murder,
conspiracy to commit murder, possession of narcotics with intent to
sell and altering the serial numbers of guns.
   They were held on $250,000 bond and were scheduled to be
arraigned Monday.
   The incident Friday night in this city 80 miles northeast of New
York City probably was drug-related, Griffin said. The men
apparently were after someone they argued with a few days ago, he
said.
   About a dozen people, including several pregnant women, were on
the street when the two gunmen appeared, police said.
   ``They walked up to the crowd and pulled out the guns. People
heard the guns being cocked and began running. Both weapons jammed.
The guys ran off,'' Griffin said. ``We were lucky, very lucky.''
   Police said they caught the men in the darkened basement of
nearby home with a jammed Uzi submachine gun and semiautomatic,
.38-caliber pistol.
   The guns, which had live bullets in their chambers, were taken
to the police forensic laboratory for disarming.
</TEXT>
