<SECOND>AM-Cleveland Bus Accident,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Truck Rams ``Trolley'' Bus, 18 Reported Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tractor-trailer loaded with steel coils
rear-ended a disabled tourist bus on a roadway Saturday, injuring
18 people, police said.
   The bus, known as the Lolly Trolley and designed to resemble a
trolley, was used to carry visitors on sight-seeing tours. It had
stopped because of mechanical problems in one of the lanes of the
``innerbelt'' freeway carrying traffic from Interstate 71 to I-90,
said Sgt. Kenneth Kirchner.
   He said the truck was unable to stop and struck the vehicle
around 11 a.m., pinning the driver inside his truck.
   Police said the injured _ Kirchner gave the number at 18 _ were
being carried to various hospitals in the city. There was no
immediate report of fatalities or information on the severity of
the injuries.
   Part of southbound I-71 was closed as a result of the accident.
