<FIRST>r a AM-Thomson-List     09-30 0297</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Thomson-List,0351</SECOND>
<HEAD>List Of Major Works of the Late Virgil Thomson</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Obit-Thomson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of some of the musical works and
books by Virgil Thomson:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   OPERAS:
   Four Saints in Three Acts (completed 1928, produced 1934).
   The Mother of Us All (1947).
   Lord Byron (completed 1968, produced 1972).
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ORCHESTRAL WORKS:
   Symphony on a Hymn Tune (1928).
   Symphony No. 2 (an orchestration of Piano Sonata No. 1, 1931).
   Portraits for Orchestra (1937-1944).
   The Seine at Night (1947).
   Wheat Field at Noon (1948).
   Concerto for Cello and Orchestra (1950).
   Sea Piece with Birds (1952).
   Concerto for Flute, Strings, Harp, and Percussion (1954).
   Autumn, a concertino for harp, strings and percussion (1964).
   Symphony No. 3 (1972).
   Thoughts for Strings (1981).
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   CHAMBER WORKS:
   Sonata da Chiesa, for clarinet, trumpet, viola, horn and
trombone (1926).
   Capital Capitals, for four men's voices and piano (1927).
   Stabat Mater, for soprano and string quartet (1931).
   Serenade, for flute and violin (1931).
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   SOLO VOCAL and CHORAL COMPOSITIONS:
   Five Songs from William Blake, for baritone and orchestra (1951).
   Praises and Prayers, for soprano and piano (1963).
   The Feast of Love, for baritone and orchestra (1964).
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   BALLETS:
   Filling Station (1937).
   The Harvest According (1952).
   Parson Weems and the Cherry Tree (1975).
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   FILM SCORES:
   The Plow That Broke the Plains (1936).
   The River (1937).
   The Spanish Earth (with Marc Blitzstein, 1937).
   Tuesday in November (1945).
   Louisiana Story (1948). (winner of Pulitzer in 1949).
   The Goddess (1957).
   Power Among Men (1959).
   Journey to America (1964).
   
   BOOKS:
   The State of Music (1939, revised 1961).
   The Musical Scene (1945).
   The Art of Judging Music (1948).
   Music Right and Left (1951).
   Virgil Thomson (autobiography, 1966).
   Music Reviewed 1940-1954 (1967).
   American Music Since 1910 (1971).
   A Virgil Thomson Reader (1981).
</TEXT>
</DOC>
