<FIRST>r i AM-Peru-Cabinet     09-30 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Peru-Cabinet,0176</SECOND>
<HEAD>Garcia Names New Prime Minister</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Alan Garcia on Saturday named
Foreign Minister Guillermo Larco Cox to also serve as prime
minister.
   Larco Cox replaced Luis Alberto Sanchez who resigned Thursday as
prime minister to campaign for re-election to the Senate.
   Garcia said Larco Cox would continue in the post of foreign
minister and also carry out the duties of prime minister.
   It is the second time Larco Cox has served as prime minister in
Garcia's four-year-old government.
   Sanchez became prime minister last May 15. He was required by
the constitution to resign by Oct. 8 to be eligible for next
April's election.
   In a customary gesture, the other ministers in the 15-member
Cabinet offered their resignations after Sanchez resigned. Garcia
said he would name the new Cabinet within the next few days after
he confers with Larco Cox. Most of the members are expected to be
reconfirmed.
   Garcia's term ends July 28, 1990. He is barred by the
constitution from seeking re-election.
</TEXT>
