<HEAD>Mob Invades Jail, Kills Two Murder Suspects</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mob of more than 1,000 people in
a rural town invaded a police station Saturday and beat to death
two prisoners suspected of killing a 19-year-old girl, according to
a television report.
   The O Globo television network said the mob assault occurred in
Santa Maria da Vitoria, 840 miles northeast of Rio.
   It reported the police station and five police cars were damaged
during the attack. It gave no further details.
